articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The number of Americans filing new claims for unemployment benefits unexpectedly fell last week, pointing to persistent strength in the labor market.
articles.title: US weekly jobless claims unexpectedly fall

articles.author: Jody Godoy
articles.description: A Florida venture capitalist, his brother and an employee accused of insider trading before a blank check company's proposed merger with former U.S. President Donald Trump's social media company pleaded not guilty in a New York court on Thursday.
articles.title: Three plead not guilty to insider trades before Trump Media deal

articles.author: Raphael Satter
articles.description: Hackers and propagandists are wielding artificial intelligence (AI) to create malicious software, draft convincing phishing emails and spread disinformation online, Canada's top cybersecurity official told Reuters, early evidence that the technological revolution sweeping Silicon Valley has also been adopted by cybercriminals.
articles.title: Exclusive: AI being used for hacking and misinfo, top Canadian cyber official says

articles.author: Noel Randewich
articles.description: China's frail growth could weigh on companies with exposure to the world's second-largest economy, including Apple (AAPL.O), big chipmakers and luxury retailers as they report quarterly results in the next few weeks.
articles.title: China's sagging economy looms over quarterly results around the world

articles.author: Christopher Bing, Raphael Satter
articles.description: A North Korean government-backed hacking group penetrated an American IT management company and used it as a springboard to target an unknown number of cryptocurrency companies, according to two sources familiar with the matter.
articles.title: Exclusive: N. Korea hackers breached US IT company in bid to steal crypto-sources

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Twitter, which has asked a court to terminate a consent order struck last year with the Federal Trade Commission (FTC) related to data breaches, said in a court filing on Thursday that it planned to subpoena Senator Elizabeth Warren in connection with the fight.
articles.title: Twitter to subpoena Senator Elizabeth Warren over communications with U.S. agencies

articles.author: David Shepardson
articles.description: U.S. Transportation Secretary Pete Buttigieg said the department was investigating why Delta Air Lines (DAL.N) passengers remained on board a plane at the Las Vegas airport that sat on the tarmac in extreme heat on Monday, citing reports that the plane sat there for four hours.
articles.title: US investigating why Delta passengers remained on plane in extreme heat

articles.author: Timour Azhari, Anna Ringstrom
articles.description: Hundreds of protesters stormed the Swedish embassy in central Baghdad in the early hours of Thursday morning, scaling its walls and setting it on fire in protest against the expected burning of a Koran in Sweden.
articles.title: Swedish embassy in Baghdad stormed, set alight over Koran burning

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russia warned that ships sailing to Ukraine's Black Sea ports from Thursday will be seen as potential military targets, days after its withdrawal from a safe-passage deal that threatens to worsen global food supplies.
articles.title: Russia warns ships in Black Sea, Ukraine to create temporary grains export route

articles.author: Moira Warburton, Josephine Walker
articles.description: The top Republican in the U.S. House of Representatives said on Thursday he did not promise Donald Trump that he would pass a measure aimed at expunging the former president's two impeachments.
articles.title: Top US House Republican denies deal with Trump to expunge impeachments
